      "rdfs:comment": [
        "DEFINITION: Something that occurs over a period of time, often characterized as an activity being carried out by some person, organization, or software application or brought about by natural forces.",
        "NOTE: An event does not necessarily have either planned or actual start or end datetimes. For example, a conference can be in the planning phase without any dates selected, but is nevertheless an (unscheduled) event. The subclasses of gist:Event state particular restrictions on planned and actual start and end dates.",
        "NOTE: An event occurs during a time interval, which is distinct from the event.",
        "EXAMPLE: A transaction, conference, baseball game, earthquake."
      ],
      "rdfs:isDefinedBy": {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/semanticarts/ontology/gistCore14.1.0"
      },
      "rdfs:label": "Event",
      "skos:definition": "Something that occurs over a period of time, often characterized as an activity being carried out by some person, organization, or software application or brought about by natural forces.",
      "skos:example": "A transaction, conference, baseball game, earthquake.",
      "skos:prefLabel": "Event",
      "skos:scopeNote": [
        "An event occurs during a time interval, which is distinct from the event.",
        "An event does not necessarily have either planned or actual start or end datetimes. For example, a conference can be in the planning phase without any dates selected, but is nevertheless an (unscheduled) event. The subclasses of gist:Event state particular restrictions on planned and actual start and end dates."
      ]
